---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/Eyebrow.astro';
import Rule from '../components/Rule.astro';
import { BOOK } from '../data/book';

const lastUpdated = '30 April 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How the-agentic-cmo.com handles personal data. Plain-language statement, UK GDPR compliant."
>
  <section class="grid-5-7" style="padding: 64px 0 48px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 5fr 7fr; gap: 80px; align-items: end;">
    <div>
      <Eyebrow>Reference</Eyebrow>
      <h1 style="font-size: 64px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 24px 0 0; line-height: 1.04; font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-serif); letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Privacy.
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 0; max-width: 520px;">
        The short version: I collect as little as possible, I never sell it, and you can ask for it back or have it deleted at any time.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--fg-muted); margin: 20px 0 0;">
        Last updated: <span class="mono">{lastUpdated}</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Rule strong margin="16px 0 0" />

  <article class="privacy-body" style="padding: 64px 0; max-width: 720px; font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--fg);">
    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">1. Who I am</h2>
    <p>This site is published and operated by Francesco Federico to support the book {BOOK.title}. For the purposes of UK and EU data-protection law, the data controller is Francesco Federico, contactable at <a href="mailto:privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com">privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com</a>.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">2. What I collect</h2>
    <p>I collect personal data in only two circumstances:</p>
    <p><strong>When you request the Cited. PDF.</strong> The form on <a href="/cited/">/cited</a> asks for an email address, an optional role, and an optional answer to "what are you trying to solve". I collect these fields only.</p>
    <p><strong>When you subscribe to the newsletter.</strong> The Chronicles of Change subscribe form is hosted by Substack. Their privacy policy applies; this site does not store newsletter subscriber data directly.</p>
    <p>I do not run third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking pixels. I do not place cookies for tracking purposes. The site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages, which logs request metadata for routine operations and security; that log is held by Cloudflare under their <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">3. Why I hold it</h2>
    <p>I hold your email address for the limited purpose of sending you the document you requested and one short follow-up email three weeks later asking what you tried. The lawful basis is your <em>consent</em> (Article 6(1)(a) UK GDPR), expressed by completing and submitting the form. Your role and "what are you trying to solve" answers, where given, help me improve the manual; they are stored alongside the email address.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">4. Where it sits</h2>
    <p>The Cited. request data is stored in Cloudflare KV (a key-value store hosted in the United Kingdom and the European Union). Email delivery is handled by Resend (resend.com), which acts as a data processor on my behalf under a data-processing agreement. Resend stores the recipient address and message metadata only for the period required to deliver and audit the email.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">5. How long I keep it</h2>
    <p>Cited. request data is retained for twelve months from the date of submission, after which it is deleted automatically. If you ask me to delete it earlier — by emailing <a href="mailto:privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com">privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com</a> — I will do so within thirty days.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">6. Who I share it with</h2>
    <p>I do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties for marketing purposes. Your data is processed by:</p>
    <ul style="margin: 16px 0; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — site hosting and KV storage.</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email delivery for the PDF.</li>
      <li><strong>Substack</strong> — newsletter delivery, only if you separately subscribe to Chronicles of Change.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These are technical service providers acting on my written instructions. I do not transfer your personal data outside the UK or EEA except where covered by the appropriate Standard Contractual Clauses or an adequacy decision.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>Under UK GDPR and the EU GDPR you have the right to:</p>
    <ul style="margin: 16px 0; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li>request a copy of the personal data I hold about you (right of access);</li>
      <li>have it corrected (right to rectification);</li>
      <li>have it deleted (right to erasure);</li>
      <li>withdraw your consent at any time, with effect from withdrawal;</li>
      <li>object to processing or request that processing be restricted;</li>
      <li>lodge a complaint with the UK Information Commissioner's Office (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>) or the relevant supervisory authority in your member state.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com">privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com</a>. I aim to respond within seven days and in any event within thirty.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">8. Cookies</h2>
    <p>This site does not set tracking cookies. The only cookies that may be set are technical cookies issued by Cloudflare for security and rate-limiting (such as <code>__cf_bm</code>); these are essential to the site's operation and are not used for analytics or profiling.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">9. Children</h2>
    <p>This site is not directed at, and I do not knowingly collect personal data from, anyone under sixteen.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">10. Changes to this notice</h2>
    <p>If I make material changes to how I handle personal data, I will update this page and refresh the "last updated" date at the top. The current version is always at <a href="/privacy/">the-agentic-cmo.com/privacy</a>.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size: 28px; color: var(--ff-slate-blue); margin: 48px 0 16px;">11. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions, complaints, or data-subject requests: <a href="mailto:privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com">privacy@the-agentic-cmo.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-body p { max-width: 100%; }
  .privacy-body a { color: var(--ff-vermillion); }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .grid-5-7 { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; gap: 32px !important; }
    h1 { font-size: 44px !important; }
    h2 { font-size: 22px !important; }
  }
</style>
